data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF 10 will append a number to disambiguate. This generates a migration renaming columns.

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** Your `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City` — now it maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin the old column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sb =>
    {
        sb.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
        // ... other properties
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, sb =>
    {
        sb.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, pb =>
    {
        pb.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, ab =>
        {
            ab.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

Or, if you prefer the new naming, just run `dotnet ef migrations add FixComplexTypeColumns` and apply it.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, etc.) now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Fix:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    {
        // Use logCommandText for safe logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Add this parameter to **every** method you implement from that interface.
